	  <concept id="i1122848"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">4.605</ph> Procedures.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d222e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d224e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Procurement Instrument Identifier (PIID)</i>. Agencies shall have in place a process that ensures that each PIID reported to FPDS is unique Governmentwide, for all solicitations, contracts, blanket purchase agreements, basic agreements, basic ordering agreements, or orders in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1121451.dita#i1121451"
                        base="i1121451"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">4.1601</xref> to <xref href="FAR-i1121496.dita#i1121496"
                        base="i1121496"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">4.1603</xref>, and will remain so for at least 20 years from the date of contract award. Other pertinent PIID instructions for FPDS reporting can be found at <xref href="https://www.fpds.gov"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">https://www.fpds.gov</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d224e38" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Unique entity identifier</i>. The contracting officer shall identify and report a unique entity identifier for the successful offeror on a contract action. The unique entity identifier shall correspond to the successful offeror's name and address as stated in the offer and resultant contract, and as registered in the System for Award Management in accordance with the provision at <xref href="FAR-i1063838.dita#i1063838"
                        base="i1063838"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.204-7</xref>, System for Award Management. The contracting officer shall ask the offeror to provide its unique entity identifier by using either the provision at <xref href="FAR-i1063809.dita#i1063809"
                        base="i1063809"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.204-6</xref>, Unique Entity Identifier, the provision at <xref href="FAR-i1063838.dita#i1063838"
                        base="i1063838"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.204-7</xref>, System for Award Management, or the provision at <xref href="FAR-i52_212-1.dita#i52_212-1"
                        base="i1060447"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.212-1</xref>, Instructions to Offerors-Commercial Items. (For a discussion of the Commercial and Government Entity (CAGE) Code, which is a different identifier, see <xref href="FAR-i1121256.dita#i1121256"
                        base="i1121256"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  4.18</xref>.)</p>
				        </li>
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d224e66" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Generic entity identifier.</p>
					          <ol id="d222e72" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d224e76" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The use of a generic entity identifier should be limited, and only used in the situations described in paragraph (c)(2) of this section. Use of a generic entity identifier does not supersede the requirements of provisions <xref href="FAR-i1063809.dita#i1063809"
                              base="i1063809"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.204-6</xref>, Unique Entity Identifier or <xref href="FAR-i1063838.dita#i1063838"
                              base="i1063838"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.204-7</xref> System for Award Management (if present in the solicitation) for the contractor to have a unique entity identifier assigned.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d224e91" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Authorized generic entity identifiers, maintained by the Integrated Award Environment (IAE) program office (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/105036</xref>), may be used to report contracts in lieu of the contractor's actual unique entity identifier only for—</p>
							              <ol id="d222e100" class="- topic/ol ">
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d224e104" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    Contract actions valued at or below $30,000 that are awarded to a contractor that is-</p>
									                  <ol id="d222e110" class="- topic/ol ">
										                    <li class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d224e114" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        A student;</p>
										                    </li>
										                    <li class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d224e123" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        A dependent of either a veteran, foreign service officer, or military member assigned outside the United States and its outlying areas (as defined in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                                          base="i1125359"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>); or</p>
										                    </li>
										                    <li class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d224e135" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        Located outside the United States and its outlying areas for work to be performed outside the United States and its outlying areas and the contractor does not otherwise have a unique entity identifier;</p>
										                    </li>
									                  </ol>
								                </li>
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d224e146" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    Contracts valued above $30,000 awarded to individuals located outside the United States and its outlying areas for work to be performed outside the United States and its outlying areas; or</p>
								                </li>
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d224e155" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    Contracts when specific public identification of the contracted party could endanger the mission, contractor, or recipients of the acquired goods or services. The contracting officer must include a written determination in the contract file of a decision applicable to authority under this paragraph (c)(2)(iii).</p>
								                </li>
							              </ol>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d224e168" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            American Recovery and Reinvestment Act actions. The contracting officer, when entering data in FPDS, shall use the instructions at <xref href="https://www.fpds.gov"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">https://www.fpds.gov</xref> to identify any action funded in whole or in part by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (Pub. L. 111-5).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d224e180" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Office codes</i>. Agencies shall by March 31, 2016—</p>
					          <ol id="d222e186" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d224e193" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Use the Activity Address Code (AAC), as defined in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                              base="i1125359"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>, assigned to the issuing contracting office as the contracting office code, and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d224e205" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Use the AAC assigned to the program/funding office providing the predominance of funding for the contract action as the program/funding office code.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
